.TH vbasic-server 1 "Zanna" "vbasic-server" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vbasic-server \- Zanna BASIC language server for LSP and MCP clients
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vbasic-server
[\fB--mcp\fR|\fB--lsp\fR] [\fB--help\fR] [\fB--version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBvbasic-server\fR exposes Zanna BASIC compiler services over the Language
Server Protocol for editors and the Model Context Protocol for AI assistants.
.PP
When no protocol flag is supplied, the server auto-detects the protocol from
the first message on standard input.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--mcp\fR
Run using newline-delimited MCP JSON-RPC transport.
.TP
\fB--lsp\fR
Run using Content-Length-framed LSP JSON-RPC transport.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Show command help and exit.
.TP
\fB--version\fR
Show version information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start MCP mode
.nf
vbasic-server --mcp
.fi
.TP
Start LSP mode
.nf
vbasic-server --lsp
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBzanna\fR(1), \fBvbasic\fR(1), \fBzia-server\fR(1)
